This paper proposes a type system and type checker to enforce secure object initialization in Java, which is a topic related to programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the risks of not following secure coding practices, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed solution involves static analysis, which is related to systems and control (cs.SY) and logic in computer science (cs.LO).
